Class MetaDataException

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class MetaDataException
extends RuntimeException

A metadata exception is thrown to indicate that an application has attempted to access a metadata object in an inappropriate way. For example, trying to access a non-existent metadata fragment of a composite metadata object will yield such an exception.

Since:
1.1
